message.content: Let $x$ be the number of students enrolled last year. This year, the enrollment is $x+\frac{4}{100}x=x\left(1+\frac{4}{100}\right)=x(1.04)$. We set this expression equal to $598$ and solve: $$1.04x = 598.$$Dividing both sides by $1.04$ gives $x = \frac{598}{1.04} = \boxed{575}$ students.
